OL,5,Cbirthday
OL,7,FReflecting on his actions, Mr Brignall
OL,8,Frecalled his motivation to protect
OL,9,FCity Hall, stating: "I was only a
OL,10,Fteenager, and I didn't have any fear.
OL,11,FI just wanted to make sure the bomb
OL,12,Fdidn't do any damage."
OL,14,FDriven to contribute further to the
OL,15,Fwar effort, Mr Brignall served as an
OL,16,Fofficial fire-watcher and later joined
OL,17,Fthe RAF, participating in crucial
OL,18,Foperations like Operation Varsity in
OL,19,F1945.
