OL,7,FDespite his remarkable courage, Mr
OL,8,FBrignall's only concern at the time
OL,9,Fwas a sore jaw and a ruined suit from
OL,10,Fcarrying sandbags up the roof.
OL,12,FMr Brignall's son Ian said: "He's
OL,13,Falways been a modest man and rarely
OL,14,Ftalked about his warJrecord. We only
OL,15,Fknew of his heroics in Cardiff on that
OL,16,Fday because he'd kept some newspaper
OL,17,Fcuttings from the time."
